<p>How to Create A Custom Peer Group</p>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>From the <strong>BankAnalytics Dashboard</strong> click <strong>CREATE PEER GROUP </strong>from the "Manage Peers" menu at the&nbsp;bottom left of page.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Search from the "Bank Find" options on the left side of page:</p>
        <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
            <li>
                <p>Select a State from the <strong>Location</strong> dropdown (use additional criteria to shorten your list, if any apply).&nbsp;</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click the <strong>Search</strong> button at the bottom of the page to view the banks in your selected State.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Click the <strong>Export Entire List</strong> link on the right side of the page to view the list in excel.</p>
                <ol style="list-style-type: lower-roman;">
                    <li>
                        <p>Use the list and the available criteria to select the banks in your peer group.&nbsp; Move all your selected banks into a new excel tab.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Copy the <strong>RSSD</strong> numbers in column D</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Move back to the <strong>MANAGE PROFILES</strong> app, and select <strong>Create New Peer Group</strong> in the top-right corner of the page.</p>
                <ol style="list-style-type: lower-roman;">
                    <li>
                        <p>Paste the <strong>RSSD</strong> numbers into the <strong>Quck Start</strong> box in the center of the page.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Type your peer group name in the <strong>Enter a name for this Peer Group</strong> box.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Select "Yes" to Save as the Default custom peer group.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Click the <strong>Save Peer Group</strong> button.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>Depending on the number of banks, the system could take up to 5 minutes to consolidate the peer group data.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>The Custom peer group is now listed in your "Peer Groups" tab of the <strong>MANAGE PROFILES</strong> app.</p>
        <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
            <li>
                <p>To edit the Peer Group, select the <strong>Edit Peer Group</strong> button or click the peer group name directly.</p>
                <ol style="list-style-type: lower-roman;">
                    <li>
                        <p>To remove banks from your peer group, simply uncheck the box(es) to the right of the desired bank(s), and click <strong>Save Peer Group.</strong></p>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <p>To add banks, click the <strong>Add More Banks To This Peer Group</strong> button in the top-right of the page.</p>
                        <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
                            <li>
                                <p>Search by the available criteria and select <strong>Search</strong>.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Check the box(es) next to the banks to add, then click the <strong>Add Selected Banks</strong> button.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Repeat steps until all banks are added to the peer group list.</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <p>Click <strong>Save Peer Group&nbsp;</strong>to complete add function.</p>
                            </li>
                        </ol>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>Other features available:</p>
        <ol style="list-style-type: lower-alpha;">
            <li>
                <p><strong>Delete Peer Group</strong> by selecting button on the right of the Peer Group box.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Can <strong>Save to Favorites</strong> banks within the Peer Group, when in Edit/View peer group.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Can change <strong>Default peer group</strong> status, when in Edit/View peer group.</p>
            </li>
        </ol>
    </li>
</ol>

